-- Tishman Speyer Is Looking for Land in Istanbul, Vatan Reports
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-04-04T06:12:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/tishman-speyer-is-looking-for-land-in-istanbul-vatan-reports.html
Tishman Speyer Properties LP, which
owns  New York ’s Rockefeller Center, is looking for land in
Istanbul’s business district to build an  office tower , Vatan
reported, citing Emre Yazici, a founding partner at TNL real
estate developers.  Tishman, which may invest as much as $500 million, is in
talks with Turkish real-estate developers including TNL to find
land between the business districts of Maslak and Levent,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 